Title: Silas
Type: Character
Source: V4

===

~ Fleur's guardian. Former Order member and healer. Never seen on screen after the prologue. The moral centre of the story in absentia.

Carried two fears in equal measure for a decade: that the Alderman would find her, and that she would push Fleur through the hard thresholds of training and make another Kestrel. She steered around those thresholds every time, believing she was being careful. She was being afraid. She didn't know they were the same thing.

She stole the Book of Demons from Kestrel in the middle of a war — not to keep its power, but to stop what was coming. She watched the person she was closest to approach the threshold where discipline ends and consumption begins, and she removed the temptation. She stopped the woman she loved by abandoning her. She has spent ten years living with that.

Her last words to Fleur: "You are what I should have been." The crack in those words is what sends Fleur to the Book.

Her example — quiet, unglamorous service despite fear, grinding herbs for people who cross the street to avoid her — is the lesson that reasserts itself in Fleur during the fire. Not the knowledge she withheld. The practice she gave every day without words.
